## Release Process

### Pre-Release Checklist
- [ ] {% if include_tests %}All tests passing{% else %}All commands manually tested{% endif %}

{% if include_linting %}- [ ] No lint errors
{% endif %}
- [ ] Version updated in `internal/version/version.go`
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated
- [ ] Documentation current
{% if init_git %}- [ ] All changes committed
{% endif %}

### Version Numbering (Semantic Versioning)
- **MAJOR:** breaking CLI changes (2.0.0)
- **MINOR:** new commands/flags, backward compatible (1.1.0)
- **PATCH:** bug fixes (1.0.1)

### Release Steps
1. Update `internal/version.Version` (or plan to set it via `-ldflags` at build time)
2. Update CHANGELOG.md - move Unreleased items to a new version section
3. Commit and tag:
   ```bash
   git commit -am "chore: release version {{ project_version }}"
   git tag v{{ project_version }}
   git push origin main --tags
   ```
4. Build release binaries:
   ```bash
   GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o dist/{{ project_name | snake_case }}-linux-amd64 ./cmd
   GOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o dist/{{ project_name | snake_case }}-darwin-arm64 ./cmd
   GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o dist/{{ project_name | snake_case }}-windows-amd64.exe ./cmd
   ```

## Debugging Guide

### Common Issues

**"declared and not used" / "imported and not used":**
- Go treats these as compile errors, not warnings - remove the unused code or reference it explicitly

**Command not found after `go install`:**
- Check `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin`) is on your `PATH`

{% if has_config_file %}
**Configuration not loading:**
- Verify the config file path passed to `config.Load`
- Check `{{ config_format }}` syntax is valid
{% endif %}

### Debug Tools

**Delve debugger:**
```bash
dlv debug ./cmd -- hello World
```

**Print debugging:**
```go
fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "DEBUG: value = %+v\n", value)
```

{% if has_logging %}
**Verbose logging:**
```bash
go run ./cmd --verbose hello World
```
{% endif %}

